# Multiplayer_Design

## 1. Applies when
PvP, co-op, matchmaking, party systems, ranking, lobbies, or server rules.

## 2. This document owns
Modes; party rules; matchmaking; ranking; lobbies; win/lose conditions; respawn;
anti-cheat needs; multiplayer balance boundaries.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Core weapon/ability numbers (Gameplay / Weapon_Balance); map layout (Map_Design);
monetization.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Modes · 3. Party & matchmaking · 4. Ranking · 5. Lobbies ·
6. Win/lose & respawn · 7. Anti-cheat needs · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Multiplayer vs Balance — mode rules vs weapon/ability numbers.
- Map vs Mode Rules — layout vs mode-specific rules.
- Multiplayer vs Technical — gameplay rules vs netcode/sync requirements.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Mode rules not mixed with map rules.
- Rank / matchmaking / progression boundaries respected.
